The paper deals with pruning deep convolutional neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of knowledge distillation, which is a technique commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to pruning that involves a budget-aware objective function, which could potentially fall under the category of neural engineering (cs.NE).
